1
00:00:08,220 --> 00:00:10,940
♪Hush now, don't disturb
the moonlight on the pond♪

2
00:00:11,940 --> 00:00:14,900
♪A shattered heart
rests pillowed in my chest♪

3
00:00:15,660 --> 00:00:17,580
♪I would shield you♪

4
00:00:17,580 --> 00:00:20,580
♪From this cruel wind and frost♪

5
00:00:22,980 --> 00:00:25,460
♪The russet cloth
brushes against my heart♪

6
00:00:26,420 --> 00:00:29,260
♪Like sunset
draping over your shoulders♪

7
00:00:30,020 --> 00:00:31,580
♪This lingering afterglow♪

8
00:00:31,580 --> 00:00:35,420
♪Holds the image
of our very first glance♪

9
00:00:36,460 --> 00:00:40,100
♪I borrow a thousand-year wind
to caress your gauze window♪

10
00:00:40,460 --> 00:00:44,420
♪Tailoring moonlight
into your luminous gown♪

11
00:00:44,900 --> 00:00:50,820
♪Severing the past,
weaving a thousand yards of splendor♪

12
00:00:51,380 --> 00:00:54,980
♪With a thousand-year dream,
I seek the fragrance of your hair♪

13
00:00:55,220 --> 00:00:58,700
♪Pouring a lifetime of passion
into the silk you wear♪

14
00:00:59,660 --> 00:01:05,660
♪In this splendid world,
wherever you are is paradise♪

15
00:01:05,980 --> 00:01:12,460
=The Silk Master from the Future=

16
00:01:12,500 --> 00:01:17,420
=Episode 13=

17
00:01:18,200 --> 00:01:20,480
I'll just compose another one,
nice and easy.

18
00:01:21,680 --> 00:01:23,280
Listen up.

19
00:01:27,880 --> 00:01:30,680
How often does the bright moon appear?

20
00:01:31,080 --> 00:01:34,400
Wine cup in hand, I ask the azure sky.

21
00:01:35,080 --> 00:01:37,800
Tonight, in the celestial palaces above,

22
00:01:39,680 --> 00:01:42,720
I wonder, what year is it
by the immortal's count?

23
00:01:44,600 --> 00:01:48,480
I long to ride the wind and return,

24
00:01:49,600 --> 00:01:52,800
yet fear those towers
of jade and crystal,

25
00:01:54,520 --> 00:01:55,320
so high above,

26
00:01:57,360 --> 00:01:58,800
would be too cold to bear.

27
00:01:59,520 --> 00:02:00,480
Bravo!

28
00:02:00,480 --> 00:02:02,760
So high above, would be
too cold to bear. What a line.

29
00:02:03,080 --> 00:02:05,480
Li, your talent
will shine through the ages,

30
00:02:05,480 --> 00:02:07,120
rivalling the sun and moon.

31
00:02:09,680 --> 00:02:11,640
It drifts past vermilion chambers,

32
00:02:11,640 --> 00:02:13,880
dips low through carved lattice windows,

33
00:02:14,480 --> 00:02:16,520
shining upon the sleepless.

34
00:02:18,480 --> 00:02:19,880
The moon should bear no grudge.

35
00:02:22,280 --> 00:02:25,680
So why is it always full
when loved ones are apart?

36
00:02:27,080 --> 00:02:29,680
People have their joys and sorrows,
partings and reunions,

37
00:02:30,600 --> 00:02:34,160
the moon waxes and wanes,
dims and shines bright.

38
00:02:35,160 --> 00:02:39,000
Nothing in this world
has ever been perfect.

39
00:02:39,720 --> 00:02:42,920
I only wish that we may live long,

40
00:02:44,520 --> 00:02:48,880
and share this moonlight
across a thousand miles.

41
00:02:48,880 --> 00:02:49,480
What a poem!

42
00:02:49,480 --> 00:02:50,320
- So exquisite!
- Superb!

43
00:02:50,880 --> 00:02:52,320
- Wonderful!
- Wonderful indeed!

44
00:02:53,120 --> 00:02:54,560
- So impressive!
- Such a fine poem!

45
00:02:58,240 --> 00:02:58,960
Ugh, Hey!

46
00:02:58,960 --> 00:02:59,680
What's going on here?

47
00:02:59,680 --> 00:03:00,480
Mr. Chen!

48
00:03:00,480 --> 00:03:01,520
- What's going on?
- What's the matter?

49
00:03:01,520 --> 00:03:02,960
Mr. Chen!

50
00:03:03,040 --> 00:03:04,200
What's happening here?

51
00:03:04,200 --> 00:03:05,000
Mr. Chen!

52
00:03:05,400 --> 00:03:06,840
Mr. Chen!

53
00:03:07,280 --> 00:03:08,040
Are you alright?

54
00:03:08,520 --> 00:03:08,960
You...

55
00:03:08,960 --> 00:03:09,640
You are...

56
00:03:12,160 --> 00:03:13,240
What's all this?

57
00:03:15,040 --> 00:03:16,480
Is this twitching thing
contagious or what?

58
00:03:17,280 --> 00:03:18,080
Guards!

59
00:03:18,080 --> 00:03:19,480
Drag these two useless fools out!

60
00:03:19,680 --> 00:03:20,480
- Understood.
- Right away.

61
00:03:27,480 --> 00:03:28,440
Drag them out!

62
00:03:31,360 --> 00:03:32,320
You worthless idiot!

63
00:03:38,080 --> 00:03:39,040
Li Yunhe,

64
00:03:39,480 --> 00:03:40,400
do you truly mean to make an enemy

65
00:03:40,400 --> 00:03:42,400
of the entire Marquis House?

66
00:03:43,240 --> 00:03:44,520
My lord,

67
00:03:44,960 --> 00:03:47,480
I'm afraid the wine has gone to my head,

68
00:03:47,480 --> 00:03:48,440
and I'm slightly tipsy.

69
00:03:48,440 --> 00:03:50,040
Only now do I realize

70
00:03:50,040 --> 00:03:51,360
that I may have
inadvertently offended you.

71
00:03:51,360 --> 00:03:52,640
We're just sharing poetry
and building friendships.

72
00:03:52,640 --> 00:03:53,920
Let's not let it spoil
the good atmosphere.

73
00:03:56,640 --> 00:03:58,320
Poetry and friendships?

74
00:03:58,320 --> 00:04:00,240
What do you even amount to

75
00:04:00,240 --> 00:04:02,360
to dare to call yourself
a friend of mine?

76
00:04:02,480 --> 00:04:03,280
Humph.

77
00:04:03,360 --> 00:04:04,320
Guards!

78
00:04:07,760 --> 00:04:09,120
Throw this piece of trash

79
00:04:09,120 --> 00:04:10,240
out of my sight!

80
00:04:10,240 --> 00:04:11,000
Hold it right there.

81
00:04:14,960 --> 00:04:15,760
What's this?

82
00:04:16,720 --> 00:04:18,080
Does the Prefect's Office

83
00:04:18,160 --> 00:04:19,440
intend to make an enemy

84
00:04:19,440 --> 00:04:20,440
of the Marquis House?

85
00:04:21,320 --> 00:04:22,040
My lord,

86
00:04:22,360 --> 00:04:23,440
the Prefect said

87
00:04:23,440 --> 00:04:25,440
Li Yunhe has rendered a great service
with his strategies.

88
00:04:25,680 --> 00:04:27,560
He urges you not to make a mistake here.

89
00:04:30,720 --> 00:04:31,520
Li Yunhe,

90
00:04:32,840 --> 00:04:35,120
the Prefect's men
can shield you for a moment,

91
00:04:35,240 --> 00:04:36,840
but they cannot protect you forever.

92
00:04:38,240 --> 00:04:39,160
You'd better start praying

93
00:04:39,160 --> 00:04:41,120
that you never let me get you.

94
00:04:41,680 --> 00:04:42,600
Or else...

95
00:04:43,880 --> 00:04:44,680
Humph.

96
00:04:45,640 --> 00:04:46,640
We're leaving.

97
00:05:02,040 --> 00:05:04,360
Farewell, young lord.

98
00:05:16,480 --> 00:05:18,720
(The heir to the Marquis of Zhennan)

99
00:05:18,720 --> 00:05:20,640
(targets me again and again.)

100
00:05:20,640 --> 00:05:21,800
(He really thinks he can just)

101
00:05:21,800 --> 00:05:23,360
(push me around?)

102
00:05:23,680 --> 00:05:25,040
(We'll see who has the last laugh.)

103
00:05:26,920 --> 00:05:29,240
This poetry gathering
was truly worth attending.

104
00:05:29,240 --> 00:05:30,320
This drama here

105
00:05:30,320 --> 00:05:32,360
is far more entertaining
than the theater.

106
00:05:32,840 --> 00:05:34,360
Mr. Li is amazing.

107
00:05:35,040 --> 00:05:36,320
As for Mr. Lu...

108
00:05:37,520 --> 00:05:38,040
I must

109
00:05:38,200 --> 00:05:40,000
let my father hear this poem

110
00:05:40,000 --> 00:05:41,040
about sorrow too.

111
00:05:44,640 --> 00:05:45,440
Yu,

112
00:05:45,880 --> 00:05:46,640
let's go.

113
00:05:46,640 --> 00:05:48,080
We should be heading back too.

114
00:05:53,320 --> 00:05:54,840
Mr. Li, please stay a moment.

115
00:05:55,840 --> 00:05:57,520
Miss Xue requests an audience with you.

116
00:05:58,120 --> 00:05:58,920
She...

117
00:06:01,160 --> 00:06:01,960
Ms. Sun,

118
00:06:02,720 --> 00:06:04,160
please pass along a message for me.

119
00:06:04,160 --> 00:06:05,000
Tell her

120
00:06:05,000 --> 00:06:06,680
I'm grateful
for the esteemed invitation,

121
00:06:06,920 --> 00:06:09,040
but I have

122
00:06:09,040 --> 00:06:10,840
little interest
in such worldly pleasures.

123
00:06:11,040 --> 00:06:11,840
I must respectfully decline.

124
00:06:12,680 --> 00:06:13,560
Might I ask,

125
00:06:13,560 --> 00:06:14,920
who is this lady?

126
00:06:15,320 --> 00:06:16,640
That's none of your concern, Ms. Sun.

127
00:06:16,640 --> 00:06:17,640
Let's go,

128
00:06:17,880 --> 00:06:18,240
Yu.

129
00:06:24,560 --> 00:06:26,280
Since you're not one for romance,

130
00:06:26,320 --> 00:06:28,000
how about I take your place

131
00:06:28,000 --> 00:06:29,040
and meet with Miss Xue

132
00:06:29,040 --> 00:06:29,920
on your behalf?

133
00:06:30,120 --> 00:06:30,520
Sure.

134
00:06:30,520 --> 00:06:31,240
No.

135
00:06:33,720 --> 00:06:35,160
Looks like you don't have a choice

136
00:06:35,160 --> 00:06:36,720
but to meet Miss Xue.

137
00:06:37,040 --> 00:06:37,840
You...

138
00:06:39,360 --> 00:06:40,240
I'm not going.

139
00:06:40,480 --> 00:06:41,320
Li Yunhe,

140
00:06:41,320 --> 00:06:43,240
if you don't see Miss Xue,

141
00:06:43,440 --> 00:06:45,040
the reward of half of Xianquan Tavern

142
00:06:45,040 --> 00:06:46,040
is off the table!

143
00:06:46,440 --> 00:06:47,240
What? You...

144
00:06:48,040 --> 00:06:49,240
But if you do go,

145
00:06:49,240 --> 00:06:50,520
the entire Xianquan Tavern

146
00:06:50,520 --> 00:06:51,760
will be all yours.

147
00:06:52,440 --> 00:06:52,840
Well...

148
00:06:52,840 --> 00:06:54,160
Still no.

149
00:06:57,120 --> 00:06:57,920
Li Yunhe,

150
00:06:58,360 --> 00:06:59,840
what if I told you I have a way

151
00:06:59,840 --> 00:07:01,320
to get the Gambiered Silk

152
00:07:01,320 --> 00:07:02,920
back on the imperial tribute list?

153
00:07:02,920 --> 00:07:03,400
If you can...

154
00:07:03,400 --> 00:07:04,440
You should go.

155
00:07:04,560 --> 00:07:05,360
Huh?

156
00:07:05,760 --> 00:07:06,840
I trust you.

157
00:07:08,240 --> 00:07:09,040
Well...

158
00:07:12,560 --> 00:07:14,200
Wait here for me.

159
00:07:14,200 --> 00:07:15,200
I'll be back before you know it.

160
00:07:15,520 --> 00:07:16,320
Alright.

161
00:07:17,040 --> 00:07:17,920
I trust you.

162
00:07:17,920 --> 00:07:18,720
Alright.

163
00:07:19,960 --> 00:07:20,760
This way, please.

164
00:07:22,360 --> 00:07:23,440
You were bluffing.

165
00:07:30,240 --> 00:07:31,080
Come here.

166
00:07:31,080 --> 00:07:32,160
My little beauty.

167
00:07:39,680 --> 00:07:40,640
Mr. Li,

168
00:07:41,240 --> 00:07:42,640
Miss Xue is right inside.

169
00:08:00,000 --> 00:08:00,920
Help!

170
00:08:00,920 --> 00:08:01,960
Somebody help!

171
00:08:04,320 --> 00:08:05,160
Come quickly!

172
00:08:07,680 --> 00:08:08,920
We need help here!

173
00:08:11,840 --> 00:08:12,640
Miss Xue?

174
00:08:13,840 --> 00:08:14,680
Miss Xue!

175
00:08:15,040 --> 00:08:15,920
Mr. Li,

176
00:08:16,320 --> 00:08:17,680
if you didn't fancy Bingxiu,

177
00:08:17,680 --> 00:08:18,880
you could have simply walked away.

178
00:08:19,680 --> 00:08:21,440
Why did you have to brutally murder her?

179
00:08:21,440 --> 00:08:22,720
She was already like this
when I got here.

180
00:08:22,720 --> 00:08:23,920
I didn't kill her!

181
00:08:25,720 --> 00:08:26,880
What are you all standing around for?

182
00:08:26,880 --> 00:08:27,720
Seize him!

183
00:08:27,720 --> 00:08:28,360
Call the constables!

184
00:08:28,920 --> 00:08:29,520
Wait a minute!

185
00:08:29,520 --> 00:08:30,120
(Darn it.)

186
00:08:30,240 --> 00:08:31,000
(I've been set up.)

187
00:08:31,840 --> 00:08:33,440
Ms. Sun, listen to me!

188
00:08:34,280 --> 00:08:34,840
Ms. Sun,

189
00:08:34,840 --> 00:08:35,600
we don't even know

190
00:08:35,600 --> 00:08:36,480
the full story yet.

191
00:08:36,480 --> 00:08:37,040
Logically speaking,

192
00:08:37,040 --> 00:08:38,240
there wasn't enough time for me to...

193
00:08:38,240 --> 00:08:39,480
Shut your mouth!

194
00:08:42,880 --> 00:08:43,680
Ms. Sun,

195
00:08:44,280 --> 00:08:45,480
what are you doing?

196
00:08:45,880 --> 00:08:46,680
This man

197
00:08:46,680 --> 00:08:47,840
murdered Miss Xue.

198
00:08:47,840 --> 00:08:48,760
What?

199
00:08:49,040 --> 00:08:50,240
That can't be.

200
00:08:50,440 --> 00:08:51,760
Mr. Li outwitted
the profiteering merchants

201
00:08:51,760 --> 00:08:52,720
and fought for the people.

202
00:08:52,720 --> 00:08:53,920
He's a man who cares about the nation.

203
00:08:53,920 --> 00:08:54,640
How could he possibly

204
00:08:54,640 --> 00:08:55,640
do such a thing?

205
00:08:55,640 --> 00:08:56,960
When we went in,

206
00:08:56,960 --> 00:08:58,320
Miss Xue was lying on the floor.

207
00:08:58,440 --> 00:09:00,240
He was the only one in the room.

208
00:09:00,240 --> 00:09:01,440
If he's not the killer,

209
00:09:01,440 --> 00:09:02,440
then who is?

210
00:09:03,520 --> 00:09:04,040
Well...

211
00:09:04,040 --> 00:09:04,880
Constable Xing,

212
00:09:05,160 --> 00:09:06,560
I really didn't kill her.

213
00:09:06,720 --> 00:09:07,920
When I came in just now,

214
00:09:07,920 --> 00:09:09,680
Miss Xue was already on the ground.

215
00:09:09,720 --> 00:09:11,280
What's all this racket?

216
00:09:11,440 --> 00:09:12,240
What's going on here?

217
00:09:12,880 --> 00:09:13,440
Prefect,

218
00:09:13,440 --> 00:09:14,760
Ms. Sun of Chunfeng Pavilion claims

219
00:09:14,880 --> 00:09:15,920
that Mr. Li Yunhe

220
00:09:15,920 --> 00:09:17,240
has murdered Xue Bingxiu,

221
00:09:17,240 --> 00:09:18,080
their top courtesan.

222
00:09:18,160 --> 00:09:19,160
What?

223
00:09:19,320 --> 00:09:21,120
Miss Xue is dead?

224
00:09:22,880 --> 00:09:23,680
Guards!

225
00:09:23,680 --> 00:09:25,360
Throw him in jail!

226
00:09:25,640 --> 00:09:26,200
Understood.

227
00:09:26,200 --> 00:09:27,880
Wait! Prefect,

228
00:09:27,880 --> 00:09:28,920
just let me explain!

229
00:09:28,920 --> 00:09:30,160
I really didn't kill anyone!

230
00:09:32,000 --> 00:09:32,840
I've been framed, Prefect!

231
00:09:32,840 --> 00:09:33,520
Keep quiet!

232
00:09:35,680 --> 00:09:36,280
This way.

233
00:09:47,800 --> 00:09:49,120
Li Yunhe has been arrested.

234
00:09:49,280 --> 00:09:50,080
Got it.

235
00:09:51,000 --> 00:09:52,040
Sir.

236
00:09:52,040 --> 00:09:52,840
Speak.

237
00:09:53,160 --> 00:09:54,840
An assassination attempt
was made on Xue Bingxiu.

238
00:09:54,840 --> 00:09:56,360
Her fate is currently unknown.

239
00:09:56,840 --> 00:09:57,760
And Li Yunhe?

240
00:09:58,040 --> 00:09:58,720
Mr. Li

241
00:09:58,720 --> 00:10:00,560
has been taken away
by the Prefect's Office.

242
00:10:00,560 --> 00:10:01,840
The Prefect now suspects him

243
00:10:01,840 --> 00:10:04,440
of being involved
in Xue Bingxiu's death.

244
00:10:04,840 --> 00:10:05,680
Impossible.

245
00:10:06,360 --> 00:10:07,880
Li Yunhe can't be the murderer.

246
00:10:09,720 --> 00:10:10,240
Let's go

247
00:10:10,680 --> 00:10:11,920
see what's going on.

248
00:10:14,240 --> 00:10:15,040
Li Yunhe!

249
00:10:15,520 --> 00:10:16,320
Li Yunhe!

250
00:10:16,720 --> 00:10:17,400
Ms. Zhou,

251
00:10:17,400 --> 00:10:19,120
don't interfere with official business,

252
00:10:19,120 --> 00:10:20,840
or you'll be arrested too.

253
00:10:21,040 --> 00:10:22,280
What crime has Li Yunhe committed?

254
00:10:22,760 --> 00:10:23,760
Officer.

255
00:10:26,440 --> 00:10:27,560
This is my master,

256
00:10:27,560 --> 00:10:29,240
the owner of Xianquan Tavern.

257
00:10:30,480 --> 00:10:32,680
The owner of Xianquan Tavern?

258
00:10:32,680 --> 00:10:33,440
I've heard of you.

259
00:10:33,440 --> 00:10:35,640
You're from the capital.

260
00:10:35,640 --> 00:10:37,080
I don't care
what kind of high connections

261
00:10:37,080 --> 00:10:38,480
you have back in the capital.

262
00:10:38,480 --> 00:10:39,240
But this

263
00:10:39,240 --> 00:10:40,040
is Feng City.

264
00:10:40,520 --> 00:10:42,160
If you dare obstruct official business,

265
00:10:42,360 --> 00:10:44,040
I'll throw the lot of you into jail too.

266
00:10:44,440 --> 00:10:45,640
Officer,

267
00:10:45,640 --> 00:10:47,080
please, take it easy.

268
00:10:47,360 --> 00:10:49,360
My master is just curious,

269
00:10:49,360 --> 00:10:50,240
what exactly is the crime

270
00:10:50,240 --> 00:10:52,040
Li Yunhe is accused of?

271
00:10:54,520 --> 00:10:56,240
Li Yunhe is suspected of the murder

272
00:10:56,240 --> 00:10:57,880
of Xue Bingxiu of Chunfeng Pavilion.

273
00:10:57,880 --> 00:10:58,560
That's impossible!

274
00:10:58,560 --> 00:10:59,360
Li Yunhe would never

275
00:10:59,360 --> 00:11:00,440
do such a thing.

276
00:11:00,640 --> 00:11:01,880
You arrested him without clear evidence

277
00:11:01,880 --> 00:11:03,160
and dragged him
to the government office.

278
00:11:03,160 --> 00:11:03,920
Is this how the Feng City authorities

279
00:11:03,920 --> 00:11:05,520
handle their cases?

280
00:11:08,880 --> 00:11:09,600
Li Yunhe...

281
00:11:10,240 --> 00:11:11,040
Ms. Zhou,

282
00:11:11,320 --> 00:11:12,120
calm down.

283
00:11:12,760 --> 00:11:14,400
Li Yunhe is only a suspect.

284
00:11:14,440 --> 00:11:16,040
Once the Prefect's Office
finds the truth,

285
00:11:16,320 --> 00:11:18,120
I'm sure he'll be released soon.

286
00:11:24,780 --> 00:11:26,080
(Chunfeng Pavilion)

287
00:11:26,080 --> 00:11:26,960
(Chunfeng Pavilion)
Behave!

288
00:11:26,960 --> 00:11:28,500
(Chunfeng Pavilion)

289
00:11:33,440 --> 00:11:34,400
What's going on here?

290
00:11:34,400 --> 00:11:35,480
How did someone end up dead?

291
00:11:37,040 --> 00:11:37,760
My lord,

292
00:11:37,760 --> 00:11:39,560
something seems off.

293
00:11:40,800 --> 00:11:43,440
Do you remember how many constables

294
00:11:43,440 --> 00:11:46,520
we ran into just now
at Chunfeng Pavilion?

295
00:11:46,520 --> 00:11:48,360
Counting Constable Xing,

296
00:11:48,920 --> 00:11:50,840
there should have been five.

297
00:11:50,840 --> 00:11:52,640
Now there are only two constables.

298
00:11:53,120 --> 00:11:54,840
And the ones carrying Xue Bingxiu's body

299
00:11:54,840 --> 00:11:56,360
are workers from Chunfeng Pavilion.

300
00:11:57,120 --> 00:11:58,840
You mean...

301
00:11:59,360 --> 00:12:00,200
I suspect

302
00:12:00,200 --> 00:12:02,320
Xue Bingxiu isn't dead at all.

303
00:12:06,720 --> 00:12:07,520
It's been handled.

304
00:12:13,960 --> 00:12:15,160
You useless trash!

305
00:12:15,160 --> 00:12:15,880
Does the Marquis House feed you

306
00:12:15,880 --> 00:12:16,640
for nothing?

307
00:12:17,120 --> 00:12:18,120
You can't even
handle something this small!

308
00:12:18,720 --> 00:12:19,000
Get lost!

309
00:12:27,480 --> 00:12:28,280
Utterly useless.

310
00:12:52,840 --> 00:12:53,640
Prefect,

311
00:12:54,120 --> 00:12:55,320
forgive my limited skills,

312
00:12:55,680 --> 00:12:56,960
but I'm powerless

313
00:12:56,960 --> 00:12:58,280
to treat Miss Xue's injuries.

314
00:12:59,920 --> 00:13:00,600
Even you

315
00:13:00,600 --> 00:13:02,720
can't do anything about her injuries?

316
00:13:03,200 --> 00:13:04,640
When the Reaper calls for you,

317
00:13:04,640 --> 00:13:06,080
there's no delaying.

318
00:13:06,440 --> 00:13:07,760
Miss Xue's injuries are too serious.

319
00:13:07,760 --> 00:13:09,520
Though she's clinging
to a breath of life,

320
00:13:10,120 --> 00:13:11,720
it's only a matter of time

321
00:13:11,720 --> 00:13:13,200
before her soul
descends to the underworld.

322
00:13:13,640 --> 00:13:15,440
If you couldn't do it,
you should've said so earlier.

323
00:13:15,440 --> 00:13:16,480
What a waste of time.

324
00:13:18,240 --> 00:13:19,080
(How outrageous!)

325
00:13:19,080 --> 00:13:20,720
(I'm the Chief
of the Imperial Medical Academy.)

326
00:13:20,720 --> 00:13:22,400
(You've got some poetry skills,)

327
00:13:22,400 --> 00:13:22,800
(I'll grant you that.)

328
00:13:22,800 --> 00:13:24,760
(But you think you can
beat me in medicine too?)

329
00:13:25,000 --> 00:13:26,840
Li Yunhe!
What do you think you're doing?

330
00:13:27,000 --> 00:13:28,400
Saving her life. What does it look like?

331
00:13:28,400 --> 00:13:28,840
Move aside.

332
00:13:28,840 --> 00:13:29,600
Li Yunhe, you...

333
00:13:29,760 --> 00:13:31,440
You can save Miss Xue?

334
00:13:31,440 --> 00:13:33,120
I had a 90 percent chance,

335
00:13:33,120 --> 00:13:33,800
but thanks to your dawdling,

336
00:13:33,800 --> 00:13:34,800
it's down to 50 percent now.

337
00:13:35,000 --> 00:13:36,080
Any more delays,

338
00:13:36,080 --> 00:13:37,400
and you can start preparing her funeral.

339
00:13:38,520 --> 00:13:39,400
This is a grave matter.

340
00:13:39,400 --> 00:13:40,840
I suggest you don't do anything rash.

341
00:13:41,280 --> 00:13:42,720
(If Xue Bingxiu dies,)

342
00:13:42,720 --> 00:13:43,960
(the posthumous edict she holds)

343
00:13:43,960 --> 00:13:45,080
(will be exploited by people)

344
00:13:45,080 --> 00:13:46,000
(with ill intentions.)

345
00:13:46,280 --> 00:13:47,720
(Don't make a mistake here.)

346
00:13:48,720 --> 00:13:50,040
I'm in a hurry here.

347
00:13:50,040 --> 00:13:52,000
I'm a full-fledged doctor
of Clinical Medicine.

348
00:13:52,000 --> 00:13:52,480
My...

349
00:13:52,480 --> 00:13:53,440
A doctor of what?

350
00:13:53,440 --> 00:13:54,320
What?

351
00:13:55,200 --> 00:13:56,400
If you don't want her to die,

352
00:13:56,400 --> 00:13:57,320
get out of my way

353
00:13:57,320 --> 00:13:58,720
and let me treat her.

354
00:13:58,840 --> 00:14:00,080
Hey, wait!

355
00:14:00,800 --> 00:14:02,040
Can you really heal her?

356
00:14:02,040 --> 00:14:03,120
Don't tell me you think

357
00:14:03,120 --> 00:14:04,680
I only know how to sell Gambiered Silk?

358
00:14:04,920 --> 00:14:06,200
Li Yunhe,

359
00:14:06,200 --> 00:14:07,760
if you can truly heal Miss Xue,

360
00:14:07,760 --> 00:14:11,200
I'll reward you
with 3,000 taels of silver.

361
00:14:12,400 --> 00:14:15,120
Please. That's all I've got.

362
00:14:18,120 --> 00:14:19,400
It's a deal!

363
00:14:20,120 --> 00:14:20,920
Okay!

364
00:14:21,400 --> 00:14:22,200
Okay.

365
00:14:25,600 --> 00:14:26,600
Everyone out, now.

366
00:14:52,680 --> 00:14:53,480
How is she?

367
00:14:55,000 --> 00:14:55,560
I didn't fail my mission.

368
00:14:55,560 --> 00:14:57,120
Your 3,000 taels of silver, Prefect,

369
00:14:57,120 --> 00:14:58,600
I'd say I've earned it.

370
00:14:59,000 --> 00:15:00,600
Really?

371
00:15:01,520 --> 00:15:02,360
She's alright now!

372
00:15:03,120 --> 00:15:04,640
She's really come back to life!

373
00:15:05,200 --> 00:15:06,720
How did you do it?

374
00:15:06,840 --> 00:15:07,320
Is that how you

375
00:15:07,320 --> 00:15:09,400
address a doctor of Clinical Medicine?

376
00:15:10,000 --> 00:15:11,040
Right, doctor.

377
00:15:11,520 --> 00:15:12,520
Doctor.

378
00:15:13,160 --> 00:15:15,320
I have failed
to recognize your eminence.

379
00:15:16,120 --> 00:15:17,160
I'm willing

380
00:15:17,560 --> 00:15:19,320
to pledge all my fortune

381
00:15:19,320 --> 00:15:20,640
to follow you, doctor.

382
00:15:22,920 --> 00:15:24,240
Hey, wait, what are you...

383
00:15:24,480 --> 00:15:26,800
Ugh, he's already gone.

384
00:15:28,040 --> 00:15:28,720
What...

385
00:15:28,880 --> 00:15:30,880
I'll go check on Xue Bingxiu.

386
00:15:37,060 --> 00:15:41,380
(Chunfeng Pavilion)

387
00:15:44,040 --> 00:15:45,360
Huh? What are you doing?

388
00:16:15,020 --> 00:16:18,620
♪Fine rain falls outside the pavilion♪

389
00:16:18,780 --> 00:16:21,980
♪With honors won, an old friend returns♪

390
00:16:22,500 --> 00:16:25,220
♪Who took the March rain♪

391
00:16:25,460 --> 00:16:28,820
♪To dye the silk against the skin♪

392
00:16:29,180 --> 00:16:31,980
♪Yam juice enriches the silk threads♪

393
00:16:32,140 --> 00:16:35,340
♪Weaving the Milky Way
down to the mortal world♪

394
00:16:36,220 --> 00:16:42,140
♪Needle and thread
stitch away the marks of time♪

395
00:16:42,180 --> 00:16:45,620
♪Cutting a yard of the misty rain♪

396
00:16:45,860 --> 00:16:48,700
♪Embroidering half a scroll
of earthly verses♪

397
00:16:48,860 --> 00:16:51,140
♪Where the golden honors hang high♪

398
00:16:51,140 --> 00:16:55,340
♪The clouds dance in the air♪

399
00:16:55,420 --> 00:16:58,700
♪Brewing wine, we speak of legends♪

400
00:16:58,860 --> 00:17:01,980
♪In fine liquor,
true feelings are revealed♪

401
00:17:02,500 --> 00:17:05,420
♪In this life I'd be a cloud-tailor♪

402
00:17:05,580 --> 00:17:12,100
♪Never failing the stars,
nor failing you♪

403
00:17:38,380 --> 00:17:41,900
♪Fine rain falls outside the pavilion♪

404
00:17:42,140 --> 00:17:45,300
♪With honors won, an old friend returns♪

405
00:17:45,900 --> 00:17:48,620
♪Who took the March rain♪

406
00:17:48,820 --> 00:17:52,140
♪To dye the silk against the skin♪

407
00:17:52,540 --> 00:17:55,420
♪Yam juice enriches the silk threads♪

408
00:17:55,500 --> 00:17:59,220
♪Weaving the Milky Way
down to the mortal world♪

409
00:17:59,260 --> 00:18:02,540
♪Warp and weft entwine,
one shuttle, one dream♪

410
00:18:02,540 --> 00:18:05,500
♪As seasons change♪

411
00:18:05,500 --> 00:18:09,140
♪Cutting a yard of the misty rain♪

412
00:18:09,140 --> 00:18:11,980
♪Embroidering half a scroll
of earthly verses♪

413
00:18:12,060 --> 00:18:14,620
♪Where the golden honors hang high♪

414
00:18:14,620 --> 00:18:18,700
♪The clouds dance in the air♪

415
00:18:18,700 --> 00:18:22,020
♪Brewing wine, we speak of legends♪

416
00:18:22,020 --> 00:18:25,740
♪In fine liquor,
true feelings are revealed♪

417
00:18:26,140 --> 00:18:29,260
♪Washing away
a lifetime of wear and tear♪

418
00:18:29,260 --> 00:18:32,140
♪Only for you♪

419
00:18:32,140 --> 00:18:35,740
♪On the street of golden honors,
the music rises♪

420
00:18:35,860 --> 00:18:38,620
♪The moon moves west
beyond the pavilion♪

421
00:18:38,740 --> 00:18:41,300
♪Wine runs dry, yet the revelry lingers♪

422
00:18:41,300 --> 00:18:45,380
♪In silk, I seek a kindred soul♪

423
00:18:45,380 --> 00:18:48,700
♪The rain has ceased,
clouds begin to clear♪

424
00:18:48,740 --> 00:18:52,100
♪The fragrant silk billows
under the low-hung stars♪

425
00:18:52,940 --> 00:18:58,620
♪I'd cut the clouds and morning glow
to drape over you♪

426
00:18:59,700 --> 00:19:03,820
♪A single bolt of silk becomes♪

427
00:19:05,100 --> 00:19:09,620
♪Your wedding gown♪
